<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-01-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-01-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">875.01/265: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-31T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 31,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. 1. Your No. 8, January 29, 5 p.m. and No. 6, January 25, 9 a.m. You
                            are authorized to extend recognition to the new régime in Albania and to
                            acknowledge the receipt of official notification of establishment of the
                            republic.</p>
                        <p>2. Department’s No. 1, January 9, 7 p.m. and your despatch No. 362,
                            December 12.<note n="5" xml:id="d331fn5">Neither printed.</note> When
                            above action has been taken you are authorized leave of absence as
                            requested.</p>
                        <p>3. Telegraph action taken.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>